<br>
I'm sorry for going AWOL without any word, but something came up that I needed to give some consideration to.  My partner has become aware of my involvement on this site and it has caused a major rift.  At first I was quite defiant and defensive, but after giving myself time to consider his perspective, I feel that he has a valid point.<br><br>
I originally came here to gain understanding about PTSD and I am grateful for the wealth of information I received.  Then after reading so many posts by people expressing their anger, grief and misconceptions about one another I found myself unable to keep out of the debate.  Eventually, I was trusted and accepted by a group of diverse personalities for my heart and mind... you were all very honoring and respectful of me without all the reference to gender and sexuality that often trips up friendships between men and women.<br><br>
Many of the discussions have helped me reclaim and refine many of my convictions and ideals... it was fun exercising the heart and mind together again.  It was also very rewarding to see understanding established between opposing viewpoints.<br><br>
But I was also discussing my partner without his knowledge and though he understands my need to do so, it was also very shocking and hurtful for him to read some of the posts...for that my heart aches.  I tried to justify keeping this a secret, but for someone who speaks often of honor and honesty it is a bit hypocritical for me to keep any kind of a secret from the most important man in my life...I have always contended that secrets and lies absolutely destroy a relationship.<br><br>
He says he doesn't want me to change my behavior or stop posting here on his account, but I do feel that it is the best thing to do.  I also deleted my e-mail address, because I want to take the steps necessary to reestablish trust...I feel very sad that I betrayed his trust...the very issue we have talked so much about.  It took me 44 yrs to find the love of my life...he's an incredible man with the purest heart I have ever encountered and I won't do anything more to risk that.  As I said before, he has been a great gift in my life...much of the compassion and empathy that I have expressed here for the Vietnam veteran comes from my intense heart connection to this man and I have become aware of the fact that much of it I haven't express to him.  Which brings me full circle back to my original post which said &quot;we seldom say the things we feel to the ones it matters most.&quot;  It's time to get off of the internet and start working harder at nurturing the love of my real live veteran...I have felt such incredible pride and awe of his accomplishments in life and the role he took in that war, yet it seems that I have not been good at telling him that.<br><br>
You guys have been loyal friends and I was honored that you trusted and valued my opinion.  The pack mom routine was good for a few laughs.  Although I was fully aware of my intentions here, it is difficult for him to fully comprehend (if your girlfriend or wife was joking around, philosophizing and discussing your issues with a group of men I would guess that you wouldn't be too comfortable with it either - I guess I forgot to consider that entirely).<br><br>
Take care and never lose sight of your objective here...I'd like to think that it is to promote understanding and tolerance of differing points of view while facilitating your own healing and<br>
camaraderie. <br><br>
 Please don't let one person ruin this site...the opposite of love is indifference...for an egomaniac like him that has to be the cruelest thing to do to him - I still suggest you ignore him, don't even talk about him and don't respond to anything he says.  I know he's an irresistable target, but not healthy for the objective.  I agree the hatred that vets have had to face should be exposed, but it shouldn't dominate, especially with a psychotic personality - trying to discuss issues with him is like trying to explain the profundity of the Illiad with a 4 year old, they may love the attention, but it's a waste of time...calling him names only gives him a thrill, but if you don't even read his posts he will shrivel and die.  He is not a fair example of the war protester's viewpoint - it is more the wild rantings of a sick mind.  Think about it at least.<br><br>
Thanks for all your help and support...it renewed my faith in people.<br><br>
ANNE <br><br>
 
